EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to governmental administration; establishing a
limit on contributions to the campaign of a candidate in
certain special elections; requiring certain candidates,
public officers or former public officers to notify the
Secretary of State when all unspent campaign
contributions have been disposed of; requiring a candidate
to file a notice of intent to file for candidacy with the
Secretary of State; revising provisions relating to the
personal use of contributions or unspent contributions;
revising provisions relating to the investigation and
enforcement of provisions of law relating to campaign
finance and financial disclosure statements; making
various other changes relating to campaign finance;
providing penalties; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law sets forth limitations on making, soliciting and accepting a
2 campaign contribution for a primary election, a general election or a special
3 election to recall a public officer. (Nev. Const. Art. 2, § 10; NRS 294A.100,
4 294A.115) Section 6.5 of this bill clarifies that these limits apply regardless of the
5 number of candidates for the office at the primary or general election.
